{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1774458119,"nonce":"ciHLsAbUDuNsnr2ZpvrNOKittgE=","title":"Part 1 analysis: frequency response of feedback-to-output transfer","message":"Umbrella: 297260c (Part 1)\n\n**Motivation:** Understand the frequency-domain properties of the learned feedback controller. Does training with stronger perturbations produce controllers with different bandwidth or phase characteristics?\n\n**Approach:** Use the natural Gaussian noise in feedback channels as broadband excitation. Compute FFT of feedback input and network output, then derive gain and phase spectra. Compare across models trained with different perturbation amplitudes.\n\n**Status:** Module exists at `src/rlrmp/modules/analysis/part1/freq_response.py`. Implements `FrequencyResponse` analysis class with gain/phase Bode-style plots per feedback variable (position/velocity) and coordinate (x/y).\n\n**References:** Standard systems identification / Bode analysis.","files":null}]}